1:00:10.273 --> 1:00:11.858
Two crossed keys.

1:00:12.442 --> 1:00:13.527
Do you recognize this?

1:00:14.152 --> 1:00:16.363
It's the Vatican seal.

1:00:18.073 --> 1:00:20.700
- Is it gas?
- A little gas.

1:00:20.784 --> 1:00:23.662
A little sulfur. A little death.

1:00:23.745 --> 1:00:27.040
So no smoking, huh? Stand back.

1:00:39.261 --> 1:00:40.929
It's a door. Push with me.

1:00:41.012 --> 1:00:41.847
Okay.

1:01:05.078 --> 1:01:06.037
Catacomb.

1:01:06.705 --> 1:01:08.915
This is how they would bury the dead.

1:01:21.636 --> 1:01:24.431
I understand the Vatican
sealing this place off.

1:01:26.558 --> 1:01:28.768
But why would they leave someone?

1:01:29.269 --> 1:01:32.022
The ring of the cardinal protector.

1:01:36.860 --> 1:01:40.405
He was the final hope, the last protector.

1:01:42.657 --> 1:01:46.536
It looks like he's a prisoner,
but he's not.

1:01:47.120 --> 1:01:50.332
The cage is for his own safety.

1:01:50.999 --> 1:01:57.839
They do this when an exorcism fails.
To protect against a demon's escape,

1:01:57.923 --> 1:02:01.301
to trap something
they need to remain hidden.

1:02:04.763 --> 1:02:07.807
Tomás, see if you can open this gate.

1:02:17.192 --> 1:02:22.489
"Your cardinal protector writes
to inform you of our worst fears.

1:02:22.572 --> 1:02:26.993
A great evil has taken hold
of San Sebastian Abbey.

1:02:27.077 --> 1:02:29.871
It must be buried here forever."

1:02:32.832 --> 1:02:33.708
It's locked.

1:02:34.376 --> 1:02:35.835
Then our friend here...

1:02:36.962 --> 1:02:38.380
